I think the problem is that when you build wxWidgets, you didn't use
the wx=
_dll.dsw solution.  One of the wxWidgets visual studio solutions
creates DL=
Ls and the other creates static libraries.  HyperNEAT was
built using the D=
LL version, so it tries to import all of the
functions from the dll.  If yo=
u are trying to link with the static
libraries, then these imports will thr=
ow warnings.
